Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

While the pasta cooks, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir the @water{75%ml}(for the sauce), @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @creme fraiche{150%g} into the bacon.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, once the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir through the cooked pasta, @peas{120%g} and the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

Taste and season with @salt and @ground black pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Share the creamy bacon and chicken linguine between your #bowls{}.

Top with a handful of @wild rocket{20%g} and drizzle with the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!